title: Andy’s Pub hosts Wayfaring Strangers
text:
Andy’s Pub hosts Wayfaring Strangers Oct 23, 2015 
Lincolnville — Rose & The Wayfaring Strangers will be playing at Andy’s Brew Pub Sunday, Oct. 25, from about 5:30 to 7:30 p.m. Andy’s Brew Pub is adjacent to the Lobster Pound, Route 1 at Lincolnville Beach. 
The local group’s style of music ranges from Hank Williams and Alan Jackson to Merle Haggard, with some old ‘60s rock and a little bluegrass gospel thrown in. Band members are Kim Moran of Lincolnville on flute, mandolin and vocals; Doug Teel of Rockville on guitar and vocals; Wade Graham of Lincolnville on bass; Linda Stevenson of Warren on fiddle; Scott Harrison on vocals and guitar; and Rosey Gerry of Lincolnville on vocals, banjo, guitar and autoharp. 
For reservations at Andy’s Brew Pub, call 789-5550. For more information about the band’s performances or bookings, contact Gerry at 975-5432 or roskari@gmail.com. 
Courier Publications’ A&E Editor Dagney C. Ernest can be reached at (207) 594-4401, ext. 115; or dernest@courierpublicationsllc.com.
